<Author>Jo_Wicky
<Content>Great location, excellent views The hotel is a great location in the shopping district of Ginza. Not to far to walk to underground lines, and taxi from Toyko station is cheap and only a few minutes ride away. The rooms are small but very nice and stylish. Our bathroom had a window that looked into the bedroom which could be closed for privacy but was kinda quirky. The hotel has a nice bar with big cushy chairs where we relaxed after returning to our hotel after dinner. Its a close walk to the Shiodome - try the restaurants at the top of the Caretta building, as long as you don't mind heights take the glass elevators which go up the side of the building to the 45th floor restaurants. 
