<Author>SfumatoPants
<Content>Great Value for their lower cost rooms My first time to stay at the Mitsui Ginza, and I have to say that I am impressed. I took a room on the low end (under Y20000) and was very happy about the ammenities and the bathroom. The Mitsui is around Y5000 more than my usual stay in the area, the Villa Fontaine, but the extra cost is worth the bathroom alone for me. The shower and bath are seperate and large, and very comfortable. The room is small, even slightly smaller than the usual standard of Japanese rooms. This results in there being less storage than usual. The closet is very narrow, no wardrobe, and no wall hooks upon which to put a coat. You luggage is liable to fill up any of the existing floorspace, and you clothes piled on the coffee table and chair. My only other complaint was that the toilet smelled, the washlet spout needed a proper disinfecting, and was mildewed - sloppy cleaning staff. For a room at the hight end of cost +Y25000, I may choose to go back to my old favorite, The Park Hotel Shiodome, which is truly a class act, but for a room on the lower end I heartily recommend a stay here, and will be back for another go soon. 
