<Author>sandinmyshoe
<Content>good location I selected this hotel for two reasons. Firstly, convenience, it is on the route of the airport limousine bus from Narita airport, in fact the bus stops immediatley outside the hotel. Secondly, the hotels location, a short walk into the heart of Ginza, a five minute walk to the fish markets and ease of access to other areas. The reception and staff were very helpful and friendly, all staff spoke English fluently. The hotels rooms were surpisingly spacious, extremely well equipped and immaculate. The bathrooms were also very well equipped and the room had good views from all windows. I stayed here for four nights in August and I used the hotel resteraunt for breakfast on most morinings, the quality of food was good, although there was not a wide international selection and therefore, unfortunately did not represent good value for money. Overall this hotel represents good value and is set in a good and convienent location. 
